{"term":"1984","caseName":"Eastern Air Lines, Inc. v. Mahfoud","caseLink":"https://www.oyez.org/cases/1984/83-1807","caseTranscripts":[{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - January 15, 1985","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/burger8/oral_argument_audio/18837","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sharp, you may proceed whenever you're ready.","start":0,"stop":65.395,"duration":65.4}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court:","start":65.395,"stop":68.066,"duration":2.67},{"text":"This case, like the preceding case, also is governed by the Warsaw Convention as that convention is supplemented by the Montreal Agreement.","start":68.066,"stop":79.625,"duration":11.56},{"text":"Now, the question here is whether pre-judgment interest may be awarded in excess of the limitation of liability that is set forth in those agreements.","start":79.625,"stop":88.824,"duration":9.2},{"text":"In this case, we unfortunately do have an accident.","start":88.824,"stop":93.76,"duration":4.94},{"text":"In June of 1975, Eastern Flight 66 crashed short of the runway at Kennedy International Airport in New York City.","start":93.76,"stop":103.147,"duration":9.39},{"text":"As a result of that crash, approximately 91 cases were brought in the federal courts.","start":103.147,"stop":109.643,"duration":6.5},{"text":"These cases were consolidated in the Eastern District of New York.","start":109.643,"stop":115.156,"duration":5.51},{"text":"They were consolidated for the purposes of pre-trial discovery and then a liability trial was held.","start":115.156,"stop":121.794,"duration":6.64},{"text":"Now, among these 91 cases were a number of cases involving passengers who were engaged in international carriage when the plane crashed.","start":121.794,"stop":134.259,"duration":12.46},{"text":"Now, as to these passengers... that is, those passengers who were engaged in international carriage... both the witness and the Montreal Agreement apply.","start":134.259,"stop":145.534,"duration":11.28},{"text":"Under those agreements, a carrier's liability is limited to $75,000 per passenger.","start":145.534,"stop":154.704,"duration":9.17},{"text":"In these international cases, Eastern moved for partial summary judgment.","start":154.704,"stop":161.513,"duration":6.81},{"text":"The basis of its motion was that partial summary judgment should be given in the form of an order that would limit Eastern's liability to $75,000 in the international passenger cases.","start":161.513,"stop":174.867,"duration":13.35},{"text":"In this particular case, the case involving Bernard and Odile Mahfoud, Eastern's motion was ultimately granted by the judge sitting in the Western District of Louisiana.","start":174.867,"stop":185.66,"duration":10.79},{"text":"The judge sustained Eastern's position, but he also sustained Respondent Mahfoud's position, which was that, even though the limitation of liability amounts to $75,000 pre-judgment interest may be awarded on top of that amount.","start":185.66,"stop":203.2,"duration":17.54}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"What would you say about post-judgment interest?","start":203.2,"stop":206.167,"duration":2.97}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, we think that post-judgment interest is not presented to the Court.","start":206.167,"stop":210.494,"duration":4.33},{"text":"It is a different type of award.","start":210.494,"stop":214.321,"duration":3.83},{"text":"Post-judgment interest reflects interest that is to be earned on a debt that has been liquidated.","start":214.321,"stop":220.115,"duration":5.79}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Post-judgment interest is simply interest on a debt, is it not?","start":220.115,"stop":224.192,"duration":4.08}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":224.192,"stop":224.848,"duration":0.66},{"text":"Pre-judgment interest is an element of the Plaintiff's compensatory damages.","start":224.848,"stop":230.751,"duration":5.9},{"text":"It's an effort to bring the Plaintiff's damages up to the date of judgment.","start":230.751,"stop":234.469,"duration":3.72},{"text":"Pre-judgment interest, for example, is often awarded by juries, if not by judges sitting as the trier of fact.","start":234.469,"stop":241.669,"duration":7.2},{"text":"In this case, we contend that the courts below failed to give the full intended purpose and effect to the limitation of liability found in the Warsaw Convention and the Montreal Agreement.","start":241.669,"stop":259.396,"duration":17.73},{"text":"Now, at the outset I want to make clear that the limit of liability that must be applied by the Court to this case is the limitation of liability that is contained in the Montreal Agreement, but the Montreal Agreement must be interpreted in light of its historical context as a highly specific amendment to the Warsaw Convention.","start":259.396,"stop":285.011,"duration":25.62}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sharp, would you help me by telling me where in the papers the language you rely on is found?","start":285.011,"stop":290.103,"duration":5.09}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":290.103,"stop":291.056,"duration":0.95},{"text":"On page 3 of our brief are the provisions of the Warsaw Convention.","start":291.056,"stop":299.74,"duration":8.68},{"text":"At page 4 is... sorry, 3 and 4 are the provisions of the Montreal Agreement.","start":299.74,"stop":307.471,"duration":7.73},{"text":"We have attached as an appendix to this brief a more fuller statement of the Montreal Agreement.","start":307.471,"stop":312.577,"duration":5.11},{"text":"It's sometimes more difficult to locate in the library than the Warsaw Convention.","start":312.577,"stop":317.982,"duration":5.41},{"text":"The Warsaw Convention here is the basic document.","start":317.982,"stop":324.994,"duration":7.01},{"text":"It governs international air carriage among 120 signatory nations.","start":324.994,"stop":330.18,"duration":5.19},{"text":"The Montreal Agreement, when it's applicable, is applicable because it simply makes two changes in the Warsaw Convention system.","start":330.18,"stop":340.676,"duration":10.5},{"text":"The changes are that the Montreal Agreement raises the level or the limit of liability; and the second change is that the Montreal Agreement waives one of the carriers' primary defenses.","start":340.676,"stop":354.56,"duration":13.88},{"text":"It's the Article 20 defense.","start":354.56,"stop":356.201,"duration":1.64},{"text":"Now, because the Montreal Agreement and the limit of liability in that agreement is an extension of the limit of liability found in the Warsaw Convention, it's appropriate to look first at the language of the Warsaw Convention, and the special language of limitation in that convention is found at page... or at Article 22.1, and that is at page 3 of our opening brief.","start":356.201,"stop":384.658,"duration":28.46},{"text":"Now, Article 22.1 contains three sentences, and the first sentence limits the carrier's liability to a fixed sum.","start":384.658,"stop":396.418,"duration":11.76},{"text":"The second sentence then goes on to create a narrow exception to that limit.","start":396.418,"stop":401.963,"duration":5.55},{"text":"The exception is for those nations that require defendants to make periodic payments to the plaintiff rather than making a lump sum payment to the plaintiff.","start":401.963,"stop":412.538,"duration":10.57},{"text":"And then the third sentence provides a means for raising the level of the limit, and that means is by special contract between the carrier and the passenger.","start":412.538,"stop":422.876,"duration":10.34}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"But suppose, Mr. Sharp, the Defendant used excessive delaying tactics before and during the trial and the judge decided to penalize him $5,000?","start":422.876,"stop":442.868,"duration":19.99}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, if the penalty were in the form of a sanction for a violation of court orders or court rules, we believe that that would not come within the--","start":442.868,"stop":454.582,"duration":11.71}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, weren't there some delays charged in this?","start":454.582,"stop":456.879,"duration":2.3}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"--Well, Your Honor, I don't believe there were delays charged.","start":456.879,"stop":460.252,"duration":3.37},{"text":"The courts in Louisiana, particularly the Fifth Circuit... I'm sorry, the district court in Louisiana... noted that there had been considerable passage of time.","start":460.252,"stop":470.436,"duration":10.18},{"text":"The point that the court said that we had been dilatory about was that we had raised an objection to a motion for summary judgment, but our objection was sustained in the Court of Appeals, the Second Circuit sitting, to determine that our position was in fact the correct one.","start":470.436,"stop":488.537,"duration":18.1},{"text":"I think the fundamental point to grasp here in terms of the delay is that Eastern answered this complaint approximately six weeks after it was filed.","start":488.537,"stop":498.502,"duration":9.97},{"text":"At that time we said that the Warsaw Convention and the Montreal Agreement limit our liability.","start":498.502,"stop":505.171,"duration":6.67},{"text":"At any time from that point on, had the Plaintiff chosen, he could have moved for a complete summary judgment asking the carrier to pay the sum of $75,000, and that would have extinguished the liability that Eastern had to that Plaintiff.","start":505.171,"stop":524.195,"duration":19.02},{"text":"That motion for complete summary judgment was never made in this case.","start":524.195,"stop":528.552,"duration":4.36},{"text":"The Warsaw Convention, its limitations on liability, were pressed by the carrier, not by the Plaintiffs.","start":528.552,"stop":536.049,"duration":7.5},{"text":"I wanted to return now to the first sentence in Article 21.","start":536.049,"stop":543.483,"duration":7.43},{"text":"Now, that sentence states that in the transportation of passengers the liability of the carrier for each passenger shall be limited to the sum of 125,000 francs.","start":543.483,"stop":557.259,"duration":13.78},{"text":"Now, it's important to consider here what the drafters of this sentence did.","start":557.259,"stop":562.023,"duration":4.76},{"text":"First of all, they did not place the limit on a certain part of the Plaintiff's recovery.","start":562.023,"stop":569.239,"duration":7.22},{"text":"Rather, they wrapped the limit around the concept of the carrier's liability.","start":569.239,"stop":574.784,"duration":5.54},{"text":"Now, I want to reach now beyond this first sentence a bit to discuss this idea of liability in terms of the convention as a whole.","start":574.784,"stop":584.842,"duration":10.06},{"text":"The concept of liability that is referred to in the first sentence is a liability that is to be determined by a court.","start":584.842,"stop":593.541,"duration":8.7},{"text":"It's the liability of the carrier at the time the Plaintiff's claim is reduced to a liquidated sum.","start":593.541,"stop":601.445,"duration":7.9},{"text":"That is normally when the Plaintiff's claim is reduced to judgment.","start":601.445,"stop":604.475,"duration":3.03},{"text":"The Warsaw Convention in its many parts, first of all it creates forums for the Plaintiff, jurisdiction in certain national courts.","start":604.475,"stop":614.548,"duration":10.07},{"text":"Second, it creates liability for the carrier.","start":614.548,"stop":619.078,"duration":4.53},{"text":"Third, it creates defenses for the carrier.","start":619.078,"stop":621.672,"duration":2.59},{"text":"Fourth, it incorporates national law to determine the amount of damages that may be due to the Plaintiff.","start":621.672,"stop":628.543,"duration":6.87},{"text":"The upshot is that this convention, the basic purpose of the convention, the basic effect of the convention, is to create liability and to bring that liability to judgment.","start":628.543,"stop":642.865,"duration":14.32},{"text":"And it's that liability that is covered by the limit found in Article 22.1, the first sentence.","start":642.865,"stop":651.034,"duration":8.17},{"text":"Now, we get confirmation of that position from the second sentence in Article 22.1.","start":651.034,"stop":659.719,"duration":8.69},{"text":"The second sentence we believe again confirms that the liability that must be limited is the carrier's liability at the time of the judgment.","start":659.719,"stop":670.432,"duration":10.71},{"text":"I would like to read the second sentence.","start":670.432,"stop":672.479,"duration":2.05},{"text":"Its text is that:","start":672.479,"stop":674.321,"duration":1.84},{"text":"\"Where, in accordance with the law of the court to which the case is submitted, damages may be awarded in the form of periodical payments, in that event, the equivalent capital value of said payments shall not exceed 125,000 francs. \"","start":674.321,"stop":693.142,"duration":18.82},{"text":"--125,000 francs, of course, being the limit fixed in sentence one.","start":693.142,"stop":697.374,"duration":4.23},{"text":"Now, this second sentence is the only sentence in the convention that speaks to the time value of money and also of the limitation on liability.","start":697.374,"stop":708.948,"duration":11.57},{"text":"Now, what the second sentence does is it expressly authorizes national courts to order carriers to pay out more than 125,000 francs if they do it over a period of years.","start":708.948,"stop":721.958,"duration":13.01},{"text":"But the sentence makes plain that the limit... that is, the limit contained in the first sentence... requires that these payments not exceed the capital value of 125,000 at the date of the award.","start":721.958,"stop":737.109,"duration":15.15}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"At what rates?","start":737.109,"stop":739.17,"duration":2.06}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"There is no specification of the rate.","start":739.17,"stop":742.373,"duration":3.2},{"text":"I take it at the date of judgment one would use an annuity table or the like to determine the appropriate rate for the period.","start":742.373,"stop":750.619,"duration":8.25}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that what has been done?","start":750.619,"stop":752.555,"duration":1.94}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, this is principally a procedure followed in Germany, and the minutes of the Warsaw Convention, the German delegates submit a paper that they would purchase an annuity or require the payment of an annuity under the German system.","start":752.555,"stop":766.55,"duration":14},{"text":"I gather that the civil code today of Germany also provides that.","start":766.55,"stop":770.172,"duration":3.62}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought you meant on the date of closing they would buy an annuity, whatever annuity could be provided for $75,000.","start":770.172,"stop":781.654,"duration":11.48}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, yes.","start":781.654,"stop":783.09,"duration":1.44},{"text":"I think in modern court terminology this would resemble what we call a structured settlement today.","start":783.09,"stop":789.025,"duration":5.93},{"text":"It would be an annuity purchased at the date of judgment or provided for by the Defendant at the date of judgment.","start":789.025,"stop":794.148,"duration":5.12},{"text":"Now, I want to direct the Court's attention then to another article of the convention, and that is Article 24.2.","start":794.148,"stop":802.893,"duration":8.75},{"text":"This article appears at page 4 of the reply brief, and in this article the drafters of the convention have undertaken to remind national courts that they may not apply their local laws regarding damages in a way that places some of the recovery outside of the limit.","start":802.893,"stop":822.996,"duration":20.1},{"text":"Article 24.2 states... and I'm going to interpolate here because the cross-referencing is very cumbersome.","start":822.996,"stop":831.165,"duration":8.17},{"text":"But Article 24.2 states that in the cases covered by Article 17... that is, cases involving death or bodily injury... any action for damages, however founded, can only be brought subject to the conditions and limits set out in this convention.","start":831.165,"stop":854.28,"duration":23.12},{"text":"In other words, this is the gentle reminder back to the national courts.","start":854.28,"stop":859.84,"duration":5.56},{"text":"Don't rework your damage concepts, your damage laws, in a way that attempts to circumvent the limit of liability.","start":859.84,"stop":867.524,"duration":7.68}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sharp, may I just ask on the periodic payments sentence.","start":867.524,"stop":872.069,"duration":4.54},{"text":"You refer to the fact that the amount shall not exceed the 125,000 francs as of the date of judgment.","start":872.069,"stop":878.599,"duration":6.53}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":878.599,"stop":878.974,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"It doesn't say date of judgment here.","start":878.974,"stop":880.817,"duration":1.84},{"text":"Are there cases that refer to that date?","start":880.817,"stop":882.817,"duration":2}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, I take it from the language of the text, and this is how I do it.","start":882.817,"stop":886.957,"duration":4.14},{"text":"First, you have to determine the law that is to be applied, and it's the law of the court to which the case is submitted.","start":886.957,"stop":896.187,"duration":9.23},{"text":"You can have as many as four different international form in the Montreal system.","start":896.187,"stop":902.792,"duration":6.61},{"text":"So you have to have the suit on file before you know which national law is going to apply.","start":902.792,"stop":907.979,"duration":5.19},{"text":"But then, more particularly in response to your question, it refers to damages being awarded in the forum of periodic payments.","start":907.979,"stop":917.24,"duration":9.26},{"text":"And it's the fact of the award, the awarding of damages.","start":917.24,"stop":921.613,"duration":4.37}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"But if the law in this certain place were settled the damage issue should always be computed as of the date of injury... I'm not suggesting that's the law in any state... then one could read it differently.","start":921.613,"stop":931.86,"duration":10.25},{"text":"I kind of thing that's the issue in the case, whether or not it's correct to insert the words \"from the date of judgment\".","start":931.86,"stop":938.091,"duration":6.23}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"We have no indication, in either the history drawn from the minutes of the Warsaw Convention or our own research, that there is any computing done prior to the date of judgment.","start":938.091,"stop":950.773,"duration":12.68}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"But is there any indication that that is the date from which computing should be done?","start":950.773,"stop":954.225,"duration":3.45}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, yes?","start":954.225,"stop":955.35,"duration":1.13},{"text":"I looked into the rest of the convention.","start":955.35,"stop":957.943,"duration":2.59},{"text":"It conceives of a claim that is being brought to judgment.","start":957.943,"stop":962.941,"duration":5},{"text":"The idea of liability itself must be liquidated, it must be reduced to a sum certain.","start":962.941,"stop":972.734,"duration":9.79},{"text":"When you have a limit such as they designed here, a limit of 125,000 francs, the limit is not applicable... that is, it's not able to be applied... until you know the amount of the Plaintiff's claim or the amount of the carrier's liability, that is, since it's the limit on liability.","start":972.734,"stop":993.069,"duration":20.33},{"text":"And this convention then provides the means for determining the liability in a judicial proceeding.","start":993.069,"stop":998.848,"duration":5.78},{"text":"So it's reading a number of provisions together, plus the specific language in the second sentence that speaks of awards or awarding damages, that leads me to believe that the critical point for determining the value of the limit is the time of judgment.","start":998.848,"stop":1017.529,"duration":18.68},{"text":"Now, what we conclude from the text of the Warsaw Convention is that it... first of all, it covers all elements.","start":1017.529,"stop":1039.456,"duration":21.93},{"text":"That is, the limitation on liability covers all elephants of the Plaintiff's recovery against the carrier.","start":1039.456,"stop":1044.657,"duration":5.2},{"text":"And second, as I mentioned to Justice Stevens, the limit fixes the carrier's maximum liability as of the date of the judgment.","start":1044.657,"stop":1055.669,"duration":11.01},{"text":"Now, the lower court in its ruling that pre-judgment interest can be awarded over and above the limitation of liability is inconsistent with this reading of the Warsaw Convention that I have tried to give to the Court.","start":1055.669,"stop":1075.52,"duration":19.85},{"text":"I want to turn now to the text of the Montreal Agreement.","start":1075.52,"stop":1079.409,"duration":3.89},{"text":"We think the text the Montreal Agreement confirms the fact that pre-judgment interest cannot be awarded over and above the limit of liability.","start":1079.409,"stop":1089.358,"duration":9.95},{"text":"The relevant provision in the Montreal Agreement appears at page 4 of our brief, and that provision states in part that the limit of liability for each carrier for death, wounding, or other bodily injury shall be the sum of $75,000 inclusive of legal fees and costs.","start":1089.358,"stop":1116.331,"duration":26.97},{"text":"Now, once again, the limit is wrapped around the concept of liability, the concept of the carrier's liability.","start":1116.331,"stop":1125.702,"duration":9.37},{"text":"And again, it's liability as determined after litigation.","start":1125.702,"stop":1131.341,"duration":5.64},{"text":"There is this reference to fees and legal costs.","start":1131.341,"stop":1135.574,"duration":4.23},{"text":"The limit is not by its terms restricted to certain items in a Plaintiff's recovery.","start":1135.574,"stop":1141.712,"duration":6.14},{"text":"The second point I want to make with respect to the text of the Montreal Agreement is by way of rebuttal to my opponent, and that is that Montreal's... Warsaw's limit... the limit contained in the Montreal Agreement, rather, is, like the limit contained in the Warsaw Convention, simply a limit.","start":1141.712,"stop":1170.341,"duration":28.63},{"text":"It's a ceiling.","start":1170.341,"stop":1171.418,"duration":1.08},{"text":"It is not a guarantee of recovery in the amount of $75,000.","start":1171.418,"stop":1177.478,"duration":6.06},{"text":"Now, the way to prove this point textually, I think, is by looking at the model notice that is contained in the Montreal Agreement, and that is at page A-3.","start":1177.478,"stop":1191.442,"duration":13.96},{"text":"It's the appendix to our brief.","start":1191.442,"stop":1193.659,"duration":2.22},{"text":"There the drafters of the Montreal agreement set down the notice that carriers will give to passengers, that is, the notice of limitation of liability.","start":1193.659,"stop":1208.419,"duration":14.76},{"text":"And that notice is to provide that the liability of the carrier","start":1208.419,"stop":1213.979,"duration":5.56},{"text":"\"is limited in most cases to proven damages, not to exceed $75,000. \"","start":1213.979,"stop":1223.085,"duration":9.11},{"text":"The notice makes clear that the Plaintiff must prove their damages.","start":1223.085,"stop":1228.863,"duration":5.78},{"text":"The fact that the Plaintiffs must prove their damages shows that the Montreal limit is a ceiling on liability as of the date of judgment.","start":1228.863,"stop":1239.437,"duration":10.57}]},{"speakerName":"Harry A. Blackmun","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, is there any question about that?","start":1239.437,"stop":1245.654,"duration":6.22}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"My opponent argues that what the Montreal Agreement has done is effectively created a liquidation of damages provision, and it's liquidated damages in the amount of $75,000 that are due at the time of the accident.","start":1245.654,"stop":1261.975,"duration":16.32},{"text":"I think there's a practical answer to that.","start":1261.975,"stop":1267.286,"duration":5.31},{"text":"I've tried now to give you the textual reading as to why that is not so.","start":1267.286,"stop":1272.517,"duration":5.23},{"text":"The practical answer to that is that nobody would have agreed to that provision because this limit, the $75,000 limit, not only reaches liability for wrongful death, but it reaches liability for personal injury and other bodily damage.","start":1272.517,"stop":1290.667,"duration":18.15},{"text":"The examples that the Court was working with in the preceding argument of minor, important injuries but minor injuries to a human being, would be recompensed at $75,000 per injury if one were to conclude that the limit in effect develops a liquidated damage for injuries at the time of the accident.","start":1290.667,"stop":1314.719,"duration":24.05}]},{"speakerName":"Harry A. Blackmun","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose we went to trial and came up with a verdict of $60,000.","start":1314.719,"stop":1319.468,"duration":4.75},{"text":"Would you be making the same argument about pre-judgment interest?","start":1319.468,"stop":1322.108,"duration":2.64}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":1322.108,"stop":1322.825,"duration":0.72},{"text":"You could recover pre-judgment interest.","start":1322.825,"stop":1324.372,"duration":1.55},{"text":"You could recover $15,000 worth of pre-judgment interest.","start":1324.372,"stop":1327.746,"duration":3.37}]},{"speakerName":"Harry A. Blackmun","textObjs":[{"text":"You would go along with that?","start":1327.746,"stop":1330.182,"duration":2.44}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1330.182,"stop":1331.087,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Harry A. Blackmun","textObjs":[{"text":"It isn't pre-judgment interest per se that you're concerned about?","start":1331.087,"stop":1333.822,"duration":2.73}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no, it's not.","start":1333.822,"stop":1334.603,"duration":0.78},{"text":"It's anything.","start":1334.603,"stop":1335.024,"duration":0.42},{"text":"This could be... this could be pain and suffering.","start":1335.024,"stop":1337.461,"duration":2.44},{"text":"it could be any item of the Plaintiff's injury.","start":1337.461,"stop":1340.178,"duration":2.72},{"text":"It could be lost future earnings.","start":1340.178,"stop":1342.913,"duration":2.73}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that because pre-judgment interest is really part of compensatory damages?","start":1342.913,"stop":1349.486,"duration":6.57}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, that's right, Your Honor.","start":1349.486,"stop":1352.141,"duration":2.65},{"text":"In this case it's awarded by Louisiana statute.","start":1352.141,"stop":1356.984,"duration":4.84}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And the only issue in this case does relate to pre-judgment interest?","start":1356.984,"stop":1361.482,"duration":4.5}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":1361.482,"stop":1362.013,"duration":0.53},{"text":"The fact is--","start":1362.013,"stop":1363.434,"duration":1.42}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Your deposit took care of post-judgment.","start":1363.434,"stop":1366.933,"duration":3.5}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"--Right.","start":1366.933,"stop":1367.183,"duration":0.25},{"text":"We deposited the full amount four months prior to the rendering of the judgment in this case.","start":1367.183,"stop":1373.415,"duration":6.23}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"How long has this case been in litigation?","start":1373.415,"stop":1375.788,"duration":2.37},{"text":"Something like ten years?","start":1375.788,"stop":1377.835,"duration":2.05}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe the complaint was filed in December of 1975.","start":1377.835,"stop":1382.974,"duration":5.14}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"The rule you want us to adopt certainly wouldn't encourage early settlement of airline accident claims, would it?","start":1382.974,"stop":1392.984,"duration":10.01}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor, my own position is that pre-judgment interest is not really likely to be much of an inducement to settlement on behalf of the Plaintiff or the Defendant.","start":1392.984,"stop":1405.464,"duration":12.48},{"text":"There is a case cited, the Bond case from West Virginia that is cited in our brief, where the court faces up to, how useful is pre-judgment interest as a real means for inducing settlement, and concludes that where the Defendant has a substantial defense and the Plaintiff has a substantial claim, it's likely they would take account of pre-judgment interest in settling the case, in valuing the case, but it's not likely that one or the other would take down the flag because pre-judgment interest was available.","start":1405.464,"stop":1437.155,"duration":31.69},{"text":"I think that is probably in my judgment the most realistic analysis of pre-judgment interest.","start":1437.155,"stop":1447.15,"duration":10}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"In this case it's a very significant percentage of the recovery, isn't it?","start":1447.15,"stop":1449.931,"duration":2.78}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, it is a very significant percentage of the recovery against Eastern.","start":1449.931,"stop":1454.445,"duration":4.51},{"text":"It's only a pittance of the recovery against the United States.","start":1454.445,"stop":1459.958,"duration":5.51}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I understand, but we're talking about the $75,000 recovery.","start":1459.958,"stop":1464.44,"duration":4.48}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1464.44,"stop":1464.94,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"And it was several years after the complaint was filed that you made the deposit?","start":1464.94,"stop":1469.157,"duration":4.22}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"It was just several days after the district court granted our motion limiting our liability to $75,000.","start":1469.157,"stop":1479.168,"duration":10.01},{"text":"I would say to you that our motion was opposed, and that one of the grounds that the motion was opposed on was that the limit was unenforceable in light of the Second Circuit's decision in TWA.","start":1479.168,"stop":1490.96,"duration":11.79}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"But it is true that the deposit was made several years after the claim was filed?","start":1490.96,"stop":1497.52,"duration":6.56}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, that's right.","start":1497.52,"stop":1498.302,"duration":0.78},{"text":"I want to rebut that point, Your Honor, with the fact that at any time, if the Plaintiff had chosen to move for complete summary judgment, I think it's likely that he would have prevailed on this record, and he never did.","start":1498.302,"stop":1512.967,"duration":14.67},{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, if there are no further questions by the Court, I think I would like to reserve the balance of my time.","start":1512.967,"stop":1525.977,"duration":13.01}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well.","start":1525.977,"stop":1527.368,"duration":1.39},{"text":"Mr. Farrell.","start":1527.368,"stop":1536.52,"duration":9.15}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court:","start":1536.52,"stop":1540.597,"duration":4.08},{"text":"The provisions of the Warsaw Convention, as well as the intent of the signatories to it and to the Montreal Agreement, clearly show that there never was a prohibition to exceeding the limits of liability, for the payment of interest or otherwise.","start":1540.597,"stop":1558.261,"duration":17.66},{"text":"As pointed out a moment ago--","start":1558.261,"stop":1562.385,"duration":4.12}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Just what do you incorporate in the \"or otherwise\"?","start":1562.385,"stop":1565.305,"duration":2.92}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"--The \"otherwise\" would be the payment of attorneys' fees and expenses in addition to the Warsaw limit, the initial Warsaw limit, Your Honor.","start":1565.305,"stop":1575.192,"duration":9.89},{"text":"As pointed out, the first paragraph of Article 22 does establish a liability limit of $8300.","start":1575.192,"stop":1587.828,"duration":12.64},{"text":"That second sentence of that same paragraph, however, which refers to periodical payments, does provide for interest.","start":1587.828,"stop":1599.916,"duration":12.09},{"text":"As Petitioner admits in his brief at page 14 and his reply brief at page 6, these words mean that the award for proven damages cannot exceed the Warsaw limit, but if the damages are paid over a period after they accrue an additional sum may be paid to the claimant, which the Petitioner says is time value of money, the basis for interest.","start":1599.916,"stop":1631.951,"duration":32.04}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"That's the annuity arrangement that you're speaking of, that we were speaking of before.","start":1631.951,"stop":1636.511,"duration":4.56}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Right.","start":1636.511,"stop":1637.417,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"But on the ordinary rules of construction, since they expressly talk about interest there but omit it in the previous discussion, what's the consequence of that rule of construction?","start":1637.417,"stop":1654.582,"duration":17.17}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"The consequence is, Your Honor, that no matter what you call it, interest is interest.","start":1654.582,"stop":1659.44,"duration":4.86},{"text":"And that rule provided for pre-judgment interest, or that provision.","start":1659.44,"stop":1663.048,"duration":3.61}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"If they're paid over a period of installments.","start":1663.048,"stop":1668.812,"duration":5.76}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"It would be, Your Honor--","start":1668.812,"stop":1672.559,"duration":3.75}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"As under the German arrangement.","start":1672.559,"stop":1674.434,"duration":1.88}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"--I'm not sure that was the German arrangement.","start":1674.434,"stop":1677.245,"duration":2.81},{"text":"But as we allege, Your Honor, and as we urge the Court to rule, the damages accrue at the time of death in a death case, and if you don't pay them for seven years, as was this instance, in this case, you pay interest.","start":1677.245,"stop":1698.954,"duration":21.71},{"text":"Interest is for the use of money.","start":1698.954,"stop":1701.204,"duration":2.25}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's the issue in this case, isn't it?","start":1701.204,"stop":1704.266,"duration":3.06}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"It is, Your Honor.","start":1704.266,"stop":1705.499,"duration":1.23},{"text":"Now, the signatories of Warsaw and Montreal never considered that the liability limitation was absolute.","start":1705.499,"stop":1715.792,"duration":10.29},{"text":"The Warsaw limitation was never strictly applied by the signatories other than the United States.","start":1715.792,"stop":1722.773,"duration":6.98},{"text":"Both Drion in his treatise on","start":1722.773,"stop":1727.116,"duration":4.34},{"text":"\"Limitation on Liabilities in International Air Law. \"","start":1727.116,"stop":1729.395,"duration":2.28},{"text":"at page 114 and Lowenfeld in 80 Harvard Law Review at 508 point out that the constant practice of the courts when applying the limitation provision of Warsaw was to exceed the limitation by awarding attorneys' fees and legal expenses against the airline.","start":1729.395,"stop":1751.559,"duration":22.16},{"text":"In addition, at least Belgium and France awarded interest on top of the Warsaw limit.","start":1751.559,"stop":1761.569,"duration":10.01},{"text":"No one outside the United States had previously thought that the Warsaw Convention limitation could not be exceeded by the application of domestic law.","start":1761.569,"stop":1772.987,"duration":11.42},{"text":"Now, this procedure had been going on for 25 years before the United States became aware of it at The Hague Conference in 1955.","start":1772.987,"stop":1783.265,"duration":10.28},{"text":"When the delegates did become aware of it, by their own volition they changed or had it changed so that The Hague Protocol permitted the payment of attorneys' fees and expenses on top of the limit.","start":1783.265,"stop":1802.288,"duration":19.02},{"text":"Now, this was done by the insistence of the United States that maximum recoveries were desired and that the expenses of litigation oftentimes ate up the amount of the award.","start":1802.288,"stop":1819.391,"duration":17.1},{"text":"There could be little doubt that if the issue of interest because of delay had been considered, that it would have been approved also.","start":1819.391,"stop":1828.7,"duration":9.31},{"text":"In other words, the delegates neglected to deal with the problem; they would wish to have it relieved... resolved, rather... if they had been aware of it.","start":1828.7,"stop":1839.335,"duration":10.63}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Are you suggesting we should go ahead and finish their task for them?","start":1839.335,"stop":1845.068,"duration":5.73}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I think that we don't have to do that, Your Honor.","start":1845.068,"stop":1851.784,"duration":6.72},{"text":"We are permitted by the articles of the Warsaw Convention to use domestic law, and our domestic law provides for interest on a damages award.","start":1851.784,"stop":1868.918,"duration":17.13},{"text":"We're not trying to change the Warsaw Convention in any way.","start":1868.918,"stop":1872.714,"duration":3.8}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I understood your opponent as agreeing that pre-judgment interest is awardable up to the overall limit on damages provided for under the Montreal Agreement.","start":1872.714,"stop":1886.506,"duration":13.79}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that is his position.","start":1886.506,"stop":1889.677,"duration":3.17},{"text":"It's not very consistent, however.","start":1889.677,"stop":1894.487,"duration":4.81}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I suppose that depends in part on whether you think pre-judgment interest is part of damages for compensation.","start":1894.487,"stop":1904.467,"duration":9.98}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Under the law of the United States, Justice O'Connor, and particularly under the law of the court where this case was tried, in Louisiana, pre-judgment interest is not a part of damages.","start":1904.467,"stop":1917.368,"duration":12.9}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"What law do you think we look to for determining pre-judgment interest, the state law, or is that a matter of federal law, or what is it?","start":1917.368,"stop":1927.474,"duration":10.11}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"We look to the law of the court.","start":1927.474,"stop":1931.035,"duration":3.56},{"text":"Under the articles--","start":1931.035,"stop":1931.924,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"The law of the court?","start":1931.924,"stop":1933.815,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"--The law of the court which has the case, Your Honor.","start":1933.815,"stop":1935.97,"duration":2.15}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"What do you mean, state law if it's a state case?","start":1935.97,"stop":1938.453,"duration":2.48}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"If it is a case, in this case in Louisiana in a federal court, you would look to the federal court to apply Louisiana law.","start":1938.453,"stop":1948.012,"duration":9.56},{"text":"And Louisiana law in this instance provided for pre-judgment interest.","start":1948.012,"stop":1952.978,"duration":4.97}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"How would that result in uniformity of liability, which was a primary goal of the Warsaw Convention and the Montreal Agreement?","start":1952.978,"stop":1966.193,"duration":13.21}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Liability would accrue at the time of the death in this case, and that's pursuant to the law of the United States and all jurisdictions that I know of.","start":1966.193,"stop":1978.156,"duration":11.96},{"text":"At that time damages would be established.","start":1978.156,"stop":1981.373,"duration":3.22},{"text":"If the case were worth X number of dollars, then no matter whether it took ten years to resolve it, it was still worth X number of dollars at the time of death.","start":1981.373,"stop":1991.307,"duration":9.93},{"text":"The delay in between is the period that we're actually talking about in this case, whether or not you can delay a case for seven years and still not pay anything in addition to the actual damages which accrued at the time of death.","start":1991.307,"stop":2011.565,"duration":20.26},{"text":"Does that answer your question?","start":2011.565,"stop":2016.281,"duration":4.72}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Your opponent says that you could have had a summary judgment much earlier if you just asked for it.","start":2016.281,"stop":2021.873,"duration":5.59}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think maybe he forgot that we did move for summary judgment, and Eastern opposed it.","start":2021.873,"stop":2029.228,"duration":7.36},{"text":"Now, the motion for summary judgment was made when the cases were in New York.","start":2029.228,"stop":2034.212,"duration":4.98},{"text":"This was a multi-district litigation case and it was in the Eastern District of New York.","start":2034.212,"stop":2042.303,"duration":8.09},{"text":"Both the Government and the United States... the Government here, the United States, and Eastern Air Lines were Defendants.","start":2042.303,"stop":2054.081,"duration":11.78},{"text":"Just before trial was to commence on liability the United States, pursuant to an agreement which it had made with Eastern Air Liner, decided not to contest liability.","start":2054.081,"stop":2069.059,"duration":14.98},{"text":"Now, the agreement was that Eastern would pay 60 percent of all the losses and the Government would pay 40 percent.","start":2069.059,"stop":2079.679,"duration":10.62},{"text":"But for that agreement, Eastern would get entire control over all aspects of the litigation, including settlements, trials, damages trials, whatever.","start":2079.679,"stop":2092.971,"duration":13.29},{"text":"When the Government decided not to contest liability, there obviously now was a solvent party.","start":2092.971,"stop":2104.293,"duration":11.32},{"text":"There was no reason to continue with Eastern, and the Plaintiff in the case, Respondent here, moved for summary judgment.","start":2104.293,"stop":2113.227,"duration":8.93},{"text":"Eastern opposed it, saying that, on a technical ground, saying that the Plaintiff did not have capacity to sue.","start":2113.227,"stop":2128.815,"duration":15.59},{"text":"There were several... two more appeals on this, and two years later... two years, in fact, after a judgment was rendered by the jury finding Eastern both negligent and liable... the Second Circuit agreed that there was a technical deficiency and sent the case back, said that you must give then notice so that they can decide whether or not they want to put in written papers and so forth.","start":2128.815,"stop":2164.222,"duration":35.41}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"Put you didn't file in New Orleans... I mean, in Louisiana?","start":2164.222,"stop":2168.143,"duration":3.92}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Later on, Justice Marshall, the case was remanded to Louisiana for trial on damages.","start":2168.143,"stop":2176.687,"duration":8.54}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you make any summary motions there?","start":2176.687,"stop":2180.31,"duration":3.62}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, because the damages trial then was imminent.","start":2180.31,"stop":2185.23,"duration":4.92},{"text":"After Eastern had been found negligent by jury trial and the United States was in the case, there was no reason.","start":2185.23,"stop":2192.04,"duration":6.81},{"text":"We still did not have the decision on whether or not the Plaintiff had capacity.","start":2192.04,"stop":2199.615,"duration":7.57}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we realize that Louisiana law is civil law, don't we?","start":2199.615,"stop":2203.347,"duration":3.73}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2203.347,"stop":2204.394,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"So it's impossible to get any... the 49 states to adopt civil law, so this is going to be different from the other states.","start":2204.394,"stop":2214.531,"duration":10.14}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I don't think so, Your Honor.","start":2214.531,"stop":2215.89,"duration":1.36},{"text":"The law of Louisiana in regard to, in this case, damages is very similar to every other jurisdiction.","start":2215.89,"stop":2223.933,"duration":8.04}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"That it's not damages?","start":2223.933,"stop":2225.479,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg your pardon?","start":2225.479,"stop":2228.415,"duration":2.94}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"That pre-trial interest is not damages?","start":2228.415,"stop":2230.524,"duration":2.11}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Pre-trial interest in Louisiana is not damages, that's correct.","start":2230.524,"stop":2235.225,"duration":4.7}]},{"speakerName":"Harry A. Blackmun","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Farrell, let me ask a foolish question, because I've missed something here.","start":2235.225,"stop":2243.081,"duration":7.86},{"text":"In effect, the Government has conceded liability?","start":2243.081,"stop":2246.424,"duration":3.34}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Correct.","start":2246.424,"stop":2247.439,"duration":1.01}]},{"speakerName":"Harry A. Blackmun","textObjs":[{"text":"Why don't you collect against the Government?","start":2247.439,"stop":2249.922,"duration":2.48}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"The problem was that we could not do it because the district court in New York had, in one of its decisions, had stated that it was not going to decide capacity to sue and was going to remand the Louisiana cases back to Louisiana and let the Louisiana court make that decision.","start":2249.922,"stop":2272.398,"duration":22.48},{"text":"When Eastern appealed the case... knowing very well, incidentally, that the Plaintiff did have capacity to sue either in Louisiana or in New York... the case then was in the hands of the Second Circuit and didn't come back for two years.","start":2272.398,"stop":2293.795,"duration":21.4}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask another bad question--","start":2293.795,"stop":2298.638,"duration":4.84},{"text":"--Don't you still have a claim against the Government?","start":2298.638,"stop":2301.449,"duration":2.81}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"We had the claim, Your Honor, but we had no... we could not go to trial because the capacity to sue issue was never decided, and the case was in the hands of the Second Circuit, which didn't decide it for two years.","start":2301.449,"stop":2314.443,"duration":12.99}]},{"speakerName":"Harry A. Blackmun","textObjs":[{"text":"Then the Government has not conceded liability?","start":2314.443,"stop":2318.285,"duration":3.84}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"If the Government had not conceded?","start":2318.285,"stop":2320.94,"duration":2.66}]},{"speakerName":"Harry A. Blackmun","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I'm asking has it?","start":2320.94,"stop":2323.549,"duration":2.61}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"The Government did concede... well, it didn't concede liability.","start":2323.549,"stop":2326.579,"duration":3.03},{"text":"It agreed not to contest liability; for all practical purposes, the same thing.","start":2326.579,"stop":2332.358,"duration":5.78},{"text":"Eventually damages were tried against the United States.","start":2332.358,"stop":2337.012,"duration":4.65}]},{"speakerName":"Harry A. Blackmun","textObjs":[{"text":"I guess when you say \"for all practical purposes\" I fall off and don't follow.","start":2337.012,"stop":2340.745,"duration":3.73}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"I meant that a concession of liability and an agreement not to contest it as far as the Plaintiff is concerned is not a lot different, although it has some different aspects, we agree.","start":2340.745,"stop":2354.583,"duration":13.84}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"I was going to ask you, I notice you said that Eastern knew that there was no issue about capacity, and I'm puzzled that Eastern would know it when the judge didn't know it.","start":2354.583,"stop":2362.877,"duration":8.29},{"text":"But that's not really the question I had, and that is, you talked about Eastern's negligence.","start":2362.877,"stop":2367.421,"duration":4.54},{"text":"Is that because a large number of the passengers were just domestic passengers and they were relevant to that?","start":2367.421,"stop":2371.764,"duration":4.34},{"text":"Because negligence I wouldn't understand would be relevant to your case.","start":2371.764,"stop":2374.716,"duration":2.95}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"The majority of the passengers here were domestic passengers, although there were quite a few Warsaw passengers involved.","start":2374.716,"stop":2381.339,"duration":6.62}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"And their negligence really didn't have anything to do with your client's claim, who was an international passenger?","start":2381.339,"stop":2388.021,"duration":6.68}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, at that time, since the motion for summary judgment... the district court found that our motion was proper, so we had... we were not in the trial on damages against Eastern... or on liability against Eastern.","start":2388.021,"stop":2410.452,"duration":22.43},{"text":"Our case was out of it because we had... under Warsaw, Montreal, the district court gave us judgment.","start":2410.452,"stop":2421.853,"duration":11.4},{"text":"You were asking how Eastern knew about the capacity and the Government did not.","start":2421.853,"stop":2431.412,"duration":9.56}]},{"speakerName":"John Paul Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Not the Government, the court--","start":2431.412,"stop":2433.004,"duration":1.59}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Or the court, I'm sorry, the court.","start":2433.004,"stop":2434.956,"duration":1.95},{"text":"Eastern had in its hands for two years prior to this motion certified copies of tutorship, which is the procedure in Louisiana, and letters of administration, which are the procedure in New York.","start":2434.956,"stop":2451.888,"duration":16.93},{"text":"And in addition, just two or three days before the Plaintiff's motion in the case, before Respondent's motion, Eastern had served upon him an offer of settlement, and it was served three days before.","start":2451.888,"stop":2477.472,"duration":25.58},{"text":"And in the offer of settlement, Eastern had to know that he had... or it's an admission, an admission that he was... or did have capacity to sue.","start":2477.472,"stop":2491.013,"duration":13.54},{"text":"So Eastern knew it very well.","start":2491.013,"stop":2492.544,"duration":1.53},{"text":"It had never come before the court because the court had never wanted to decide that issue.","start":2492.544,"stop":2498.12,"duration":5.58},{"text":"It was going to send it back to Louisiana.","start":2498.12,"stop":2500.666,"duration":2.55},{"text":"Now, the Petitioner states that he agrees that you can have pre-judgment interest, just so it doesn't exceed the limitation.","start":2500.666,"stop":2527.561,"duration":26.89},{"text":"I'd like to just give you an example of what the result would be if this were correct.","start":2527.561,"stop":2532.684,"duration":5.12},{"text":"If you had, for instance, a $25,000 judgment or if the damages were worth $25,000, and the airline didn't pay at for say a year and the interest rate was ten percent, he would permit the $2500 of pre-judgment interest to be added onto the amount that the airline owed the claimant.","start":2532.684,"stop":2564.545,"duration":31.86},{"text":"Now, if it were say $74,000 and the judgment was not paid until the year after and the interest was the same ten percent, the Petitioner would permit payment of interest in the amount of $1,000, but no more.","start":2564.545,"stop":2580.899,"duration":16.35},{"text":"The remaining $6,400 earned on a $74,000 damages award would remain in the pocket of the insurance company.","start":2580.899,"stop":2589.974,"duration":9.08},{"text":"Now, in the subject case, where the judgment was for $75,000 for decedent and the airline kept the money made on the investment of that amount for its own use for over seven years, the Petitioner's position would not permit any interest, even though the damages award, because of the delay, was only worth about $31,000, permitting the airline's insurers to pocket approximately $44,000 per decedent for its own account or, under its own figures, a total of $87,000.","start":2589.974,"stop":2624.6,"duration":34.63}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"--Well, that analysis would support an argument that this was not a very good treaty.","start":2624.6,"stop":2629.348,"duration":4.75}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, we're not trying to change the treaty.","start":2629.348,"stop":2633.425,"duration":4.08},{"text":"We're merely saying that the provisions of the treaty permit domestic law to be applied, but the treaty could not operate without domestic law.","start":2633.425,"stop":2646.091,"duration":12.67},{"text":"It really provides guidelines and, as this Court held in the Franklin Mint case, it's a flexible treaty.","start":2646.091,"stop":2656.899,"duration":10.81},{"text":"It wasn't meant to be narrowly construed.","start":2656.899,"stop":2661.366,"duration":4.47}]},{"speakerName":"William H. Rehnquist","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I suppose your opponents would argue that you're the one that's trying to narrowly construe it.","start":2661.366,"stop":2677.797,"duration":16.43},{"text":"I suppose the treaty, like any other treaty, is supposed to be construed in accordance with its terms, not either \"narrowly\" nor \"broadly\".","start":2677.797,"stop":2687.887,"duration":10.09}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, pre-judgment interest was never mentioned in the treaty, so we have to look to the background to see if we can interpret it properly.","start":2687.887,"stop":2700.772,"duration":12.88},{"text":"As I tried to point out in the beginning, the signatories never thought that exceeding the limitation of Warsaw was any problem.","start":2700.772,"stop":2712.72,"duration":11.95},{"text":"They all did it.","start":2712.72,"stop":2713.658,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"For attorneys' fees and costs.","start":2713.658,"stop":2716.844,"duration":3.19}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2716.844,"stop":2718.641,"duration":1.8},{"text":"Well, expenses is what they said.","start":2718.641,"stop":2720.28,"duration":1.64},{"text":"I'm not sure what \"expenses\" were.","start":2720.28,"stop":2722.045,"duration":1.76},{"text":"But the principle is the same.","start":2722.045,"stop":2725.153,"duration":3.11}]},{"speakerName":"William H. Rehnquist","textObjs":[{"text":"When did the courts of the United States first begin awarding pre-judgment interest in tort cases?","start":2725.153,"stop":2737.476,"duration":12.32}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't know, Your Honor, but it's been for a long time, and even today some courts do not.","start":2737.476,"stop":2748.643,"duration":11.17}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"When it's a jury verdict you can't really find it out, can you, if the jury takes it into account?","start":2748.643,"stop":2757.499,"duration":8.86}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor, in a case like this, in a death case, as I'm pointing out, the damages accrue at the time of death.","start":2757.499,"stop":2768.995,"duration":11.5},{"text":"So if you don't pay it, it's not in the jury's hands.","start":2768.995,"stop":2774.259,"duration":5.26},{"text":"It's a ministerial procedure that the clerk of the court says you have to pay so much interest on it until you pay it.","start":2774.259,"stop":2781.098,"duration":6.84},{"text":"It doesn't change the treaty, it doesn't change the law of damages.","start":2781.098,"stop":2785.426,"duration":4.33},{"text":"It just is a fairness, a way of proceeding.","start":2785.426,"stop":2793.626,"duration":8.2},{"text":"Now, the signatory United States never considered pre-judgment interest as an integral part of proven a damages, as Petitioner would have the Court believe.","start":2793.626,"stop":2811.727,"duration":18.1},{"text":"The United States chairman--","start":2811.727,"stop":2814.492,"duration":2.77}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Farrell, suppose the State of Louisiana passed a law and said that in all wrongful death statutes, if they involve the Warsaw Pact they shall include judgment on interest, pre-judgment interest.","start":2814.492,"stop":2830.938,"duration":16.45},{"text":"Would that be good?","start":2830.938,"stop":2832.688,"duration":1.75}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"--I would think so.","start":2832.688,"stop":2835.343,"duration":2.65},{"text":"Under the local law, it shouldn't be any problem.","start":2835.343,"stop":2837.889,"duration":2.55},{"text":"That wouldn't affect the treaty any.","start":2837.889,"stop":2839.81,"duration":1.92}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if they say that in all cases under the Warsaw Pact the state may, at its will, add $15,000 to the $75,000?","start":2839.81,"stop":2851.243,"duration":11.43}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think now you're getting into a different problem.","start":2851.243,"stop":2855.617,"duration":4.37},{"text":"You're changing now the limitation.","start":2855.617,"stop":2857.522,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, put down the same amount of money; would that be a different problem?","start":2857.522,"stop":2861.239,"duration":3.72}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"If you change... you cannot change the limitation, Justice Marshall, because only the Congress can do that, or perhaps this Court.","start":2861.239,"stop":2871.783,"duration":10.54},{"text":"But awarding interest on a judgment does not change anything in Warsaw or does not change anything in Montreal.","start":2871.783,"stop":2882.356,"duration":10.57}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"But it adds money.","start":2882.356,"stop":2883.871,"duration":1.51}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"No, it doesn't add money.","start":2883.871,"stop":2885.839,"duration":1.97},{"text":"It merely makes the award--","start":2885.839,"stop":2888.197,"duration":2.36}]},{"speakerName":"Thurgood Marshall","textObjs":[{"text":"More money.","start":2888.197,"stop":2889.775,"duration":1.58}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"--Yes, it... it makes it adequate.","start":2889.775,"stop":2894.695,"duration":4.92}]},{"speakerName":"Sandra Day O'Connor","textObjs":[{"text":"But this isn't the wording, interest on a judgment.","start":2894.695,"stop":2897.897,"duration":3.2},{"text":"We're talking about pre-judgment interest.","start":2897.897,"stop":2900.677,"duration":2.78},{"text":"So doesn't it really turn on how we characterize it, whether it's a part of compensation to the victim or not?","start":2900.677,"stop":2909.626,"duration":8.95}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, as I was going to point out, Your Honor, the United States' position at Montreal, as stated by Chairman Lowenfeld, was that recovery for death or injury would presumably be based on some combination of earning power, life expectancy, and, in the case of death, degree of dependence of the survivors.","start":2909.626,"stop":2931.773,"duration":22.15},{"text":"He didn't say anything about interest, interest being a part of damages.","start":2931.773,"stop":2938.005,"duration":6.23},{"text":"There's no express language in Warsaw or Montreal either permitting pre-judgment interest or excluding it.","start":2938.005,"stop":2946.08,"duration":8.07},{"text":"Miller in her treatise on 19, gives some insight.","start":2946.08,"stop":2960.107,"duration":14.03},{"text":"She states that:","start":2960.107,"stop":2961.246,"duration":1.14},{"text":"\"Where the convention is silent, the lex for a will determine the conditions under which the damages allegedly due may be compensated. \"","start":2961.246,"stop":2970.398,"duration":9.15}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"But there's no silence, here.","start":2970.398,"stop":2973.381,"duration":2.98},{"text":"There's a very fixed $75,000 statement.","start":2973.381,"stop":2976.974,"duration":3.59}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"I meant, Your Honor, that it's silent as to interest.","start":2976.974,"stop":2982.128,"duration":5.15},{"text":"We're not saying that you exceed the limitation.","start":2982.128,"stop":2988.266,"duration":6.14},{"text":"The limitation was the damages which were awarded for the death, the damages which accrued at the time of death.","start":2988.266,"stop":2997.295,"duration":9.03},{"text":"The interest merely is for reimbursement for the use of that money by the insurance company when it didn't pay for seven years.","start":2997.295,"stop":3008.179,"duration":10.88}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"If you had an ordinary domestic negligence case where the Defendant was insured by public liability insurance in the usual way, but the limit of the policy was $75,000... now, it is often suggested, whether true or not, that insurance companies who take over the defense of these cases delay as long as possible so they can keep getting the interest on their own money in their own bank or portfolio.","start":3008.179,"stop":3039.48,"duration":31.3},{"text":"Do you think any pre-judgment interest would be added to the $75,000 limit on liability of the insurer?","start":3039.48,"stop":3048.399,"duration":8.92}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say, Your Honor, that if it was in a jurisdiction that permitted pre-judgment interest, it always would be added.","start":3048.399,"stop":3054.989,"duration":6.59}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"In other words, the limit of the policy would go up?","start":3054.989,"stop":3057.676,"duration":2.69}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"No, the limit of the policy would stay the same.","start":3057.676,"stop":3060.393,"duration":2.72},{"text":"But the fact that they didn't pay it on time would... the interest would be awarded on top of it.","start":3060.393,"stop":3066.532,"duration":6.14}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Now you're talking about post-judgment interest.","start":3066.532,"stop":3068.75,"duration":2.22}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it would--","start":3068.75,"stop":3070.733,"duration":1.98}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Could the insurer, the insurer, be liable for any more than $75,000 on any theory at all?","start":3070.733,"stop":3083.463,"duration":12.73}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"--The insurer would only be liable for damages up to the extent of the policy.","start":3083.463,"stop":3089.054,"duration":5.59},{"text":"Again, but if he didn't pay it, if it's a death case, he was liable at the time of death for $75,000.","start":3089.054,"stop":3098.034,"duration":8.98}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, your opponent has conceded, understand it, that if they didn't pay the judgment as I they would be liable for interest on the judgment.","start":3098.034,"stop":3104.844,"duration":6.81},{"text":"I'm sure he--","start":3104.844,"stop":3106.094,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"George E. Farrell","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, he didn't get the judgment until seven years after the accident, Your Honor.","start":3106.094,"stop":3111.186,"duration":5.09},{"text":"We're saying that the amount accrues at the time of the death, and if you pay it seven years later you pay interest on it.","start":3111.186,"stop":3120.932,"duration":9.75},{"text":"If it were only an injury amounting to $5,000 and you didn't pay it for seven years, you would pay interest on the seven years, over that period of time.","start":3120.932,"stop":3130.802,"duration":9.87},{"text":"I might say that the Respondent here never did oppose the Warsaw limit, as intimated by Petitioner.","start":3130.802,"stop":3145.921,"duration":15.12},{"text":"Franklin Mint was mentioned to the district court after it was handed down in a slip opinion, to show that this was an other case.","start":3145.921,"stop":3158.245,"duration":12.32},{"text":"Franklin Mint could never have been used in this case by the court.","start":3158.245,"stop":3165.023,"duration":6.78},{"text":"It was prospective.","start":3165.023,"stop":3166.242,"duration":1.22},{"text":"It had no bearing whatsoever here.","start":3166.242,"stop":3170.801,"duration":4.56},{"text":"And I might say that, on the other side of the coin, Eastern Air Line depended upon the Domangue case, which is the basis for this decision in the Mahfoud case.","start":3170.801,"stop":3187.186,"duration":16.39},{"text":"I might conclude by saying that denying pre-judgment interest in this case would fail to effect any purpose of the convention's framers or signatories.","start":3187.186,"stop":3197.744,"duration":10.56},{"text":"The decision of the district court, as affirmed by the Court of Appeals, ensures that a Warsaw-Montreal recovery is not diminished by the simple strategy of delaying payment until the award diminishes in value.","start":3197.744,"stop":3212.41,"duration":14.67},{"text":"The judgment should be affirmed.","start":3212.41,"stop":3214.877,"duration":2.47}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you have anything further, Mr. Sharp?","start":3214.877,"stop":3221.344,"duration":6.47}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"I wanted to try briefly to clarify some of the facts relating to how this litigation was handled.","start":3221.344,"stop":3228.06,"duration":6.72},{"text":"There were 92 cases at the high water mark in the litigation.","start":3228.06,"stop":3232.62,"duration":4.56},{"text":"When the case was fixed for liability trial on September the 18th, that number had been reduced to 54.","start":3232.62,"stop":3241.243,"duration":8.62},{"text":"On September the 18th, 1978, 18 of the 54 cases were international cases of the Warsaw-Montreal variety.","start":3241.243,"stop":3252.145,"duration":10.9},{"text":"36 were domestic cases that were going to be tried on the ordinary issues of damages and negligence outside the Warsaw Convention.","start":3252.145,"stop":3261.547,"duration":9.4},{"text":"The trial counsel for Eastern was prepared for a six weeks liability trial on issues of whether the air traffic controllers and the like had caused the crash, when the Plaintiffs on the day of trial... that is, the Warsaw Plaintiffs... and in some cases on the preceding day to trial orally moved for summary judgment, for partial summary judgment in the sum... I'm sorry.","start":3261.547,"stop":3290.301,"duration":28.75},{"text":"They did not ask for $75,000.","start":3290.301,"stop":3292.267,"duration":1.97},{"text":"They just asked orally that Eastern be declared liable to them.","start":3292.267,"stop":3297.984,"duration":5.72},{"text":"Eastern did not say it was not liable for the accident under Warsaw, but it said that it was not liable to them, to the Plaintiffs; that there was an individual... there was a dispute of fact over who should be the Plaintiff.","start":3297.984,"stop":3315.087,"duration":17.1},{"text":"The reason for that was that in almost half of the international cases there were more than two human beings that were contesting for the position of representing the estate or of bringing the wrongful death claim against the estate.","start":3315.087,"stop":3330.706,"duration":15.62},{"text":"Eastern was reserving its position so that it would be liable to the proper Plaintiff and not also be liable to the improper Plaintiff.","start":3330.706,"stop":3338.609,"duration":7.9},{"text":"In the Mahfoud case there was not a contest, but the papers did not show that.","start":3338.609,"stop":3344.855,"duration":6.25},{"text":"Counsel is faced with 15 different oral motions for summary judgment.","start":3344.855,"stop":3349.761,"duration":4.91},{"text":"He takes the position, I would like to have that in writing, as Rule 56 entitles me to have it in writing.","start":3349.761,"stop":3356.025,"duration":6.26},{"text":"I would like to have ten days notice.","start":3356.025,"stop":3358.57,"duration":2.55},{"text":"In ten days he can pull together the facts and determine whether there is in fact a dispute with Mahfoud.","start":3358.57,"stop":3365.644,"duration":7.07},{"text":"That was never done.","start":3365.644,"stop":3366.957,"duration":1.31},{"text":"Now, the issue of summary judgment was revisited.","start":3366.957,"stop":3370.753,"duration":3.8},{"text":"It was revisited approximately a year later in proceedings to amend the summary judgment, and at that point... at that point the Plaintiffs moved to amend the summary judgment.","start":3370.753,"stop":3385.948,"duration":15.19},{"text":"Eastern urged the trial judge to decide the issue of capacity now.","start":3385.948,"stop":3391.134,"duration":5.19},{"text":"The trial judge did not do that.","start":3391.134,"stop":3393.634,"duration":2.5},{"text":"The Plaintiff's counsel for Mahfoud at page 41 proffered an affidavit... this is 41 of the joint appendix... proffered an affidavit, and in the affidavit they suggested that any summary judgment against Eastern make clear that Eastern is not precluded by the judgment from raising its defense of lack of capacity.","start":3393.634,"stop":3417.639,"duration":24.01},{"text":"In other words, we're trying to get the legal issues solved and they are making clear that the legal issues are reserved for another day.","start":3417.639,"stop":3425.12,"duration":7.48},{"text":"Now, I disagree with Mr. Farrell on the point concerning whether Mahfoud ever contested the application of the limit.","start":3425.12,"stop":3434.288,"duration":9.17},{"text":"There is a four-page brief in the record at pages 902 to 906... it's in the unprinted portion of the record before the Court... in which Mahfoud urges the district court to declared that the limit is unenforceable.","start":3434.288,"stop":3448.345,"duration":14.06},{"text":"I want to make two other points, and that is that counsel for the Plaintiff quite properly mentioned, after the Warsaw Convention it became evident, at least to some of the drafters at Hague and Montreal, it became evident that some courts were applying legal fees and costs above the limit, and in that event--","start":3448.345,"stop":3473.866,"duration":25.52}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Your time has expired, counsel.","start":3473.866,"stop":3476.054,"duration":2.19}]},{"speakerName":"Richard M. Sharp","textObjs":[{"text":"--Thank you, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":3476.054,"stop":3477.335,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"Warren E. Burger","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you, gentlemen.","start":3477.335,"stop":3478.13,"duration":0.8},{"text":"The case is submitted.","start":3478.13,"stop":3480.005,"duration":1.88}]}]}],"decidedBy":"Burger Court","arguedOn":"Jan 15, 1985","petitioner":"Eastern Air Lines, Inc.","respondent":"Mahfoud","docket":"83-1807","citation":"474 US 213 (1985)","justiaLink":"https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/474/213","lowerCourt":"United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit","grantedOn":"","decidedOn":"Dec 10, 1985"}